        <section class="tribute-info">
            <img src="kalam.jpg" alt="Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam">
            <p>
                Dr. Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam, widely known as A.P.J. Abdul Kalam, was an Indian scientist and politician who served as the 11th President of India from 2002 to 2007. Born on October 15, 1931, he made significant contributions to the field of aerospace engineering.
            </p>
            <p>
                Dr. Kalam played a pivotal role in the development of India's first indigenous satellite launch vehicle and ballistic missile technology. He was often referred to as the "Missile Man of India" for his exceptional work in these areas.
            </p>
            <p>
                Beyond his scientific achievements, Dr. Kalam was a beloved figure due to his inspirational speeches, humility, and dedication to education. He interacted enthusiastically with students and encouraged them to dream big and work hard to achieve their goals.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>“Dream, dream, dream. Dreams transform into thoughts and thoughts result in action.” - Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam</p>
    </footer>
